courseWork.title: Sit Spot Expectations
courseWork.description:
Find an outside spot  to observe (Being outside is preferred, however you may complete your sit spot by a window inside your house if needed.) 

 Spend 15 minutes observing the world around you

Use your senses

What do you smell? 

What do you see? 

What do you hear? 

What do you feel? 

Record your observations on a piece of paper 

Your observations can be in any format -- a list or pictures usually works best. 

Stay in one spot during the sit spot. The longer you are in one area the more you observe!

Bring a stopwatch, set a timer, or bring a watch with you to know when 15 minutes are up. 

Have fun! Be creative! 

If you are enjoying it stay longer, or move to another spot and compare! 

Bring your sit spot assignment to the next science class (on Wednesday)
